{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"dazed-daisy-bur","description":"RISK 2 (over-cap growth). `src/rebar/llm/prompts.py` crossed the soft cap this window (745 -> 827) and was ADDED to the allowlist rather than split. Split along the front-matter seam so it drops back off the allowlist.\n\n## What / files — careful split along the front-matter seam\n- Extract the front-matter I/O cluster to a NEW `src/rebar/llm/prompts_frontmatter.py` (per `docs/architecture.md:219`): `parse_front_matter`, `_split_front_matter_raw`, `write_front_matter`, `_refuse_newer_schema_version`, plus the constants `FRONT_MATTER_KEYS`, `PROMPT_SCHEMA_VERSION`, and the exception classes `PromptError`, `PromptVersionError`.\n- Re-export the public names from `prompts.py` for back-compat so existing `prompts.<name>` callers keep working.\n- The cache-split helpers that call `resolve_prompt` stay in `prompts.py` (they cannot move).\n\n## Scope\nIn: front-matter cluster extraction + re-export shim. Out: changing the prompt schema or resolution logic.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `prompts_frontmatter.py` created (>100 LOC) holding the front-matter cluster + the two exception classes.\n- [ ] `prompts.py` drops BELOW 800 LOC and is REMOVED from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt`.\n- [ ] Public symbols remain importable from `prompts.py` (re-export) — no caller breakage.\n- [ ] The prompt front-matter / drift-gate tests pass.","id":"0ef9-00e0-6bc1-4d3b","parent_id":"5ca8-5993-ca83-40f1","priority":1,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","oss-remediation"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Risk 2: split prompts.py front-matter cluster (drop off allowlist)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782605243410150001,"uuid":"b6c64e49-bf21-428e-91f5-5d72a2b512bc"}